  "texts": [
    "We will defer discussion of these more involved situations to the specific case studies, and here simply discuss the moiré translation-invariant problem.In the following, we allow intervalley coherence (breaking of U (1) v symmetry), but impose S z conservation.",
    "The latter means we restrict to spin-collinear states along the (arbitrarily chosen) z-axis in spin space.",
    "In terms of the one-body density matrix, we haveP τ ′ bs ′ k β,τ ask α ≡ ⟨ĉ † τ as (k α)ĉ τ ′ bs ′ (k β)⟩ = 0 if s ̸ = s ′ or k α ̸ = k β,(46)where τ = ±1 for valley K and K ′ respectively.",
    "This block-diagonal structure allows us to parameterize the one-body density matrix asfoot_19 P τ ′ b,τ a (k, s) ≡ ⟨ĉ † τ as (k)ĉ τ ′ bs (k)⟩.",
    "(47)Due to the block-diagonal structure of one-particle density matrix and the symmetry of the Hamiltonian, the HF Hamiltonian is also diagonal in k and s, i.e.H HF τ ask α,τ ′ bs ′ k β = δ ss ′ δ k α k β H HF τ a,τ ′ b (k α, s)(48)for some H HF τ a,τ ′ s (k α, s)."
  ]
